Why a squashed import (rather than a GitHub fork or preserved history)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The greylag-ci fork exists to run GitHub Actions that compare findings
across CI/CD security scanners against a known-vulnerable target.

GitHub forks have several limitations that would block this purpose:
  * Workflows must be re-enabled per-fork and run with read-only tokens.
  * Secrets / Code Scanning uploads behave differently across the fork
    boundary, which would distort the scanner comparison.

The upstream history was squashed into a single commit because the
upstream's *first* commit contains an intentional example PyPI token
(part of the "Duchess" challenge walkthrough) that GitHub free-tier
push protection rejects. The example token has been redacted in
solutions/duchess.md and replaced with "REDACTED-EXAMPLE-PYPI-TOKEN-
see-NOTICE". Nothing else has been modified from the upstream HEAD.

The redacted token was a teaching artifact, not a live credential.
To see the original walkthrough output verbatim, consult the upstream
repository at the SHA above.

